          "username": "shivasubedi"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2021-08-09 12:02:34.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 6:\n\n(1 comment)\n\n> I see the module_name and revision getting stored in yang_resources when a single schema set file is uploaded. Eg : cps-cavsta-onap-internal2021-01-28.yang\n> But when a zip file is saved with multiple files, it doesnt save the module_name and revision in the yang-resources table.\n\nTested it in my local environment and it saves the module_name and revision in the yang-resources table\n\n> As this story is related to fetching/listing the modules, the code changes for storing the module_name and revision could be taken as a different task.\n\nAgreed it should've been taken as a different task but for this story it was recommended to do it together, in the future I will make sure to make break up of stories into small tasks",
        "patchset_number": 6
      },
